== Pashtuns in the Middle East ==
Hundreds of thousands of Pasthuns serving as migrant workers reside in the [[Middle East]], particularly in the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Qatar]], [[Kuwait]], [[Oman]] and other Arab countries.<ref name="Pashto-UAE"/><ref name="Jaffrelot"/> Many of them are involved in the transport business, while others are employees of construction companies.

Over 100,000 Pashtuns live in [[Iran]] as citizens of that country and a further sizable number live among the Afghan refugees. The Iranian Pashtuns are mainly concentrated in the Afghan-Iran border, in the [[South Khorasan]] Province of Iran.<ref name="Ethnologue-Iran"/>

About 300,000 Pashtuns immigrated to the Gulf Countries from 1976 to 1981, representing 35% of Pakistani immigrants.<ref name=Jaffrelot>{{Cite book|title=Pakistan: nationalism without a nation?|last1=Jaffrelot|first1=Christophe |authorlink=|coauthors=|volume=|year=2002|publisher=Zed Books |location=|isbn=1842771175|page=27|pages=352|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=I2avL3aZzSEC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA27#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=2010-08-22}}</ref>

== Pashtuns in Europe ==
{{See|Afghan diaspora|Pakistani diaspora}}
Many Pashtuns have migrated from their homeland in [[Central Asia]] to [[Europe]]. The following statistics represent the number of Pashtuns in European countries:{{Citation needed|date=January 2010}}

*[[Germany]] (55,000)
*[[France]] (33,000)
*[[Austria]] (71,000)
*[[Netherlands]] (26,000)

===United Kingdom===
{{See|Afghans in the United Kingdom|British Pakistani}}
The [[United Kingdom]] is home to some 100,000 Pashtuns,<ref>{{cite news| url=http://in.reuters.com/article/southAsiaNews/idINIndia-40220620090610 | work=Reuters | title=FEATURE - Support for Taliban dives among British Pashtuns | date=2009-06-10}}</ref> making it one of the most populous overseas Pashtun communities in the world and the most populous one in the West.<ref>"The Other Languages of England", ''British Journal of Educational Studies'', Vol. 34, No. 3 (October 1986), pp. 288-289.</ref>

== Pashtuns in other parts of the world ==
=== United States ===
{{See|Afghan American|Pakistani American}}
[[File:Pashto USC2000 PHS.svg|thumb|Pashtuns in the US by state]]
Pashtuns have been present in [[California]] at least since agricultural labor was imported in the early 20th century. Since the late 1970s and onwards, Pashtuns began immigrating to the [[United States of America|USA]] in large numbers and are well established there. Pashtuns in the United States are famous for running top Afghan cuisine restaurants<ref>Helmand - [http://www.helmand.com/ Baltimore, Maryland]</ref><ref>Helmand - [http://www.helmandrestaurantsanfrancisco.com/home5SF.htm San Francisco, California]</ref><ref>Helmand - [http://www.helmandrestaurantcambridge.com/home5.htm Cambridge, Massachusetts]</ref> and as owners of the fast-food restaurant chain [[Kennedy Fried Chicken]] that is based in [[New York City]].

=== Canada ===
{{See|Afghan Canadian|Pakistani Canadian}} 
1,690 persons characterised their ethnicity as "Pashtun" in Canada's 2006 census.<ref>[http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?TPL=RETR&ALEVEL=3&APATH=3&CATNO=97-562-XCB2006006&DETAIL=0&DIM=&DS=99&FL=0&FREE=0&GAL=0&GC=99&GK=NA&GRP=1&IPS=97-562-XCB2006006&METH=0&ORDER=1&PID=92333&PTYPE=88971,97154&RL=0&S=1&ShowAll=No&StartRow=1&SUB=801&Temporal=2006&Theme=80&VID=0&VNAMEE=&VNAMEF= 2006 Census of Canada: Topic-based tabulations]</ref>

=== Australia ===
{{See|Afghan (Australia)|Afghan Australian|Pakistani Australian}}
Large numbers of Afghans were recruited in the 19th century during the initial British development of [[Australia]], especially for the operation of camel trains in desert areas.  These consisted of men who were not allowed to bring their families with them, many married local [[Australian Aborigines|Aborigines]] and are now known as [[Ghans]].<ref>[http://www.dulwichcentre.com.au/afghans.html "Afghan histories in Australia."] Dulwich Centre. Retrieved January 6, 2010.</ref> During the 1980s and 90s, Pashtuns began settling in [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]], [[Melbourne]], [[Sydney]] and other major cities of Australia.

=== Southeast Asia ===
Since the early 1900s there have been many generations of Pashtuns who migrated from Afghanistan, Pakistan and the tribal areas of Pakistan (Khyber Pakhtunkhwa). Pashtun settlements in [[Thailand]] have been common throughout the provinces. There is even a Thai-Pashtun Friendship Association. Because the Pashtuns are fiercely independent, they often are well treated and respected by the Thai locals. Countries like [[Cambodia]], [[Laos]], [[Indonesia]] and [[Malaysia]] also have similar cases of Pashtun settlements.

=== East Asia ===
There may be some Pashtun communities living in parts of [[China]], [[Taiwan]] and [[Japan]].

=== Guyana and Suriname===
{{Main article|Pakistanis in the Caribbean}}
Some people living in [[Guyana]] and [[Suriname]] claim to be of Afghan descent. Most of them moved to South American countries during the [[India]]n immigration.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://afghanland.com/culture/guyana.html|title=Afghans of Guyana|work=Wahid Momand|publisher=Afghanland.com|year=2000|accessdate=2007-01-18}}</ref>

